5. Let's create a 2D random walk with 200 steps in a 2D coordinate system. Each step on y-axis follows the normal distribution. Each step on x-axis follows an exponential distribution. You can use np.random.exponential() function to construct these steps. The exponential function contains two arguments: size of the steps (just like the normal distribution function we learned) and scale. You can set the scale = 1 (20 points).¶
